reviews.review: Well acted. The plot developed well and kept my attention and curiosity.
Very fun who done it film just like you would expect.  Great cast and a lot of good twist.  Some you can see coming others you don't.
For me, this was just O.K. I figured out several aspects of the plot. maybe that's why it wasn't as suspenseful or intriguing for me.
Loved the plot, settings and actors! Great movie!

I sort of disliked the characters but that's probably what the audience was supposed to do.  It felt like a very dumb move but I found myself engrossed in trying to figure out "who done it."   The movie was a little long so make sure you visit the restroom beforehand.  You won't want to leave during the movie in case you miss something.  While I wouldn't want to watch it a second time, I did enjoy it very much.

I just want to say if Martin Scorsese would see this one he would have no two doubts about this motion picture termed as one of the best kinds of cinema ever made.
Having said that, Marvel movies are cinema too, not his kind of cinema though!

My husband and I really enjoyed Knives Out!!  Was funny, sad, and there were lots of twists and turns to keep you guessing, which made the movie very interesting and riveting.   Would recommend this movie.  One other note, everyone was talking about the movie and how it ended on the way out of the theater, everyone seemed to really enjoy the experience.
Good Cast but predictable ending n not much of a mystery to whodunnit.

I wish I saw this before reading the reviews. Probably would have enjoyed it more. It was so pumped up I guess it couldn't have possibly matched the hype. Was just so so. No need to see on big screen.

This was the most entertaining movie I've seen all year.  The actors give great performances and the sets are exactly what you expect from a Christy-style whodunit.  I didn't think that Daniel Craig would fit in, but his southern drawl was delightful.  We were engaged by the plot from beginning to the big reveal.  A must see!
